  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The UW/VA Brain Bank stores brain tissue from deceased individuals and neurosurgical
      patients who have donated their tissue in order to aid scientific research. Through the
      collection of central and peripheral nervous tissue, as well as skeletal muscle tissue, the
      UW/VA Brain Bank hopes to participate in advancing knowledge of diseases of the nervous
      system such as Alzheimer and Parkinson disease.Brain donations are needed from healthy
      individuals, as well as those affected by diseases of the nervous system.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
